Now, please understand not all pain and suffering you and I experience is brought on by our own choices to ignore God.

23:18.402 --> 23:24.551
Some of the pain and suffering we experience is a result of the sin-filled world we live in, right?

23:25.913 --> 23:32.643
Sometimes it's the sinful choices of others that bring heartache into our lives, that bring pain into our lives.

23:33.905 --> 23:39.253
Book of Romans tells us the whole creation groans looking forward to its redemption.

23:40.695 --> 23:45.362
Some of the pain and suffering we experience is the result of sin of others.

23:46.626 --> 23:50.390
And some is the result of the sin cursed creation we live in.

23:51.992 --> 24:03.605
So to carry the attitude that all trouble or all struggle that we see in the lives of others is somehow the result of their rebellion from God.

24:03.625 --> 24:08.451
That's not biblical, it's inaccurate and it's incredibly damaging to people.

24:10.413 --> 24:14.898
But pain from others, that's not the pain and suffering that Isaiah is talking about.

24:16.706 --> 24:27.105
The pain and suffering that Isaiah is talking about is the pain and suffering that's brought onto our lives when a person stubbornly refuses to stop their rebellion from God.

24:29.430 --> 24:31.494
They stubbornly refuse to turn to him.

24:31.974 --> 24:33.457
It brings struggle.

24:33.497 --> 24:35.942
It brings heartache into their lives.

24:36.904 --> 24:40.370
At some point, God gives the rebellious person what they want.

24:40.930 --> 24:45.577
They reject God's presence and they reject his involvement in their lives.

24:45.837 --> 24:51.445
And so they allow their evil to play the role of judge and disciplinarian in their lives.

24:52.006 --> 24:55.231
In other words, their behavior brings it on themselves.

24:55.651 --> 24:57.033
Notice chapter one verse 31.

24:57.694 --> 25:05.786
The mighty man will become tender and his work a spark both will burn together with no one to quench the fire.

25:05.826 --> 25:08.530
They brought it on themselves.

25:09.218 --> 25:14.363
And if you flip over to chapter three, your second, to hear pages turning and devices changing.

25:16.645 --> 25:19.948
Chapter three, verses eight to nine, Jerusalem staggers.

25:21.109 --> 25:23.291
Judas falling.

25:23.992 --> 25:27.515
Their words and deeds are against the Lord, defying his glorious presence.

25:27.896 --> 25:31.659
Notice, the look on their faces testifies against them.

25:32.700 --> 25:35.243
They parade their sin like Sodom.

25:36.444 --> 25:38.866
They don't hide it, woe to them.

25:40.770 --> 25:45.135
In other words, they've seen the wall there, but they keep banging their head against it.

25:45.175 --> 25:48.138
They see the fire and they keep putting their hand in it.

25:50.421 --> 25:56.487
So they're bringing heartache and wounding and burning into their lives.

25:59.811 --> 26:10.002
As you and I can't ignore the fundamental wisdom and principles of life that God has designed into the world, we can't just ignore them and not get burned.

26:12.034 --> 26:19.625
You and I can't ignore God's Word in ways, in matters of life.

26:19.725 --> 26:21.788
We can't ignore His Word in matters of money.

26:22.709 --> 26:26.575
We can't ignore His Word as principles and matters of relationships, health.

26:28.598 --> 26:37.050
We can't ignore God's design in these matters and expect to not pay any consequences for that.

26:38.331 --> 26:40.114
There's natural consequences for that.

26:41.954 --> 26:45.944
God says in your rebellion, you will bring about your own destruction.

26:48.831 --> 26:54.846
The second thing a sustained pattern of rebellion brings is direct judgment of God.

26:54.866 --> 26:56.490
That's like the second phase.

26:56.911 --> 26:59.538
If the natural consequences don't wake us up,

26:59.618 --> 27:01.640
then the judgment of God comes.

27:01.921 --> 27:04.944
Look at chapter two verses six through nine.

27:05.344 --> 27:08.368
You Lord have abandoned your people, the descendants of Jacob.

27:08.628 --> 27:11.051
They are full of superstitions from the east.

27:11.291 --> 27:15.055
They practice divination like the Philistines and embrace pagan customs.

27:16.057 --> 27:18.119
Their land is full of silver and gold.

27:18.159 --> 27:19.500
There's no end of their treasures.

27:19.821 --> 27:21.463
Their land is full of horses.

27:21.543 --> 27:22.564
There's no end of their chariots.

27:22.844 --> 27:24.466
The land is full of idols.

27:24.962 --> 27:29.046
They bow down to the work of their hands to what their fingers have made.

27:29.387 --> 27:29.967
Notice for a sign.

27:30.288 --> 27:33.431
So the people will be brought low and everyone humbled.

27:36.815 --> 27:42.781
If the pain and suffering that's experienced is a natural consequence of violating God's laws, that doesn't serve to wake us up.

27:44.523 --> 27:46.405
Then the direct judgment of God is experienced.

27:48.508 --> 27:49.489
God is a loving God.

27:49.549 --> 27:50.770
Don't get me wrong.

27:51.106 --> 27:53.249
We can't even describe how loving he is.

27:53.289 --> 27:56.073
God is a loving God, but he's a holy God as well.

27:58.457 --> 28:02.082
And because he's a holy, it is impossible for him to just overlook sin.

28:02.122 --> 28:04.165
Oh, it's okay.

28:05.087 --> 28:05.928
He mean well.

28:05.968 --> 28:15.061
The very essence of his holiness requires that sin be punished.

28:17.926 --> 28:20.850
Now, here's something important to remember about the judgment of God.

28:22.434 --> 28:32.892
It is always delivered with one hope in mind, one hope in mind to serve, to discipline, train and draw people back to himself.

28:34.655 --> 28:35.917
It's always rooted in love.

28:38.121 --> 28:42.488
Notice the verses that follow the announcement of coming judgment in chapter one.

28:43.110 --> 28:43.971
Look at verse 24.

28:44.011 --> 28:45.714
Therefore the Lord, the Almighty,

28:46.562 --> 28:52.712
The mighty one of Israel declares, I will vent my wrath on my foes and avenge myself on my enemies.

28:53.012 --> 28:54.515
I will turn my hand against you.

28:54.915 --> 29:00.985
I will thoroughly purge away your dross and remove all your impurities.

29:01.045 --> 29:02.948
See, this is the purpose of the judgment.

29:03.789 --> 29:05.071
This is the purpose of the discipline.

29:06.293 --> 29:09.899
I will restore your leaders as in the days of old, your rulers as at the beginning.

29:10.300 --> 29:14.386
After you will be called the city of righteousness, the faithful city.

29:16.386 --> 29:23.637
You see, the picture is one of heating up the metals and burning out the impurities so that there's purity there.

29:28.024 --> 29:45.650
And here's the fascinating thing about Isaiah's message, both for his original hearers and for us, as clear and decisive as this penalty for rebellion that's announced, as clear as that's announced, the promise of redemption is clearly stated too.

29:46.338 --> 29:48.461
He gives them a pathway to renewal.

29:48.801 --> 29:50.864
He gives them a pathway to restoration.

29:51.444 --> 29:52.806
Look at chapter one verse 18.

29:53.187 --> 29:53.747
I love this.

29:54.088 --> 29:56.811
Come now, let's settle the matter.

29:58.233 --> 30:00.896
God says, let's get together.

30:00.916 --> 30:02.538
Let's just settle this, can we?

30:03.720 --> 30:08.666
Though your sins are like scarlet, they shall be white as snow.

30:11.149 --> 30:11.730
Right?

30:13.602 --> 30:28.622
You see, this is why we have to drag ourselves through the yuck and the muck of the negative part of this prophecy in order for the promise to be like, yes, thank God, right?

30:29.664 --> 30:34.430
Because we all know how broken we are, but here the hope comes.

30:34.450 --> 30:38.496
Though they are read as crimson, they shall be like wool.

30:38.956 --> 30:43.122
If you are willing and obedient, you will eat the good things

30:43.970 --> 30:53.159
of the land, but if you resist and rebel, you will be devoured by the sword for the mouth of the Lord has spoken it."

30:55.622 --> 30:59.526
Look at verses 27 to 28, Zion will be delivered with justice.

31:00.026 --> 31:08.935
Her penitent ones with righteousness, but rebels and sinners will both be broken and those who forsake the Lord will perish.

31:10.277 --> 31:11.698
If that's your practice,

31:12.994 --> 31:14.876
There's only doom in store.

31:17.239 --> 31:24.709
Friends, Isaiah doesn't mince any words to his audience, so it's important we don't mince any words in this moment.

31:27.112 --> 31:28.514
God says, turn to me.

31:30.537 --> 31:31.478
Turn to me, come to me.

31:33.380 --> 31:33.841
Come to me.

31:36.584 --> 31:40.189
No matter how deep the stain of sin, I will remove it.

31:40.289 --> 31:41.010
Do you hear that?

31:41.698 --> 31:45.924
No matter how deep the stain of sin, I will remove it.

31:47.146 --> 31:47.967
You said God's promise.

31:48.948 --> 31:52.774
No matter how long you've walked without me, never too late.

31:53.735 --> 31:55.778
Come, do you hear that?

31:56.519 --> 31:57.420
That's the heart of love.

31:58.462 --> 32:09.778
No matter how impure your life has been, I can cleanse you and make you as pure as freshly fallen snow.

32:10.146 --> 32:17.176
God says, I can take the dirtiest, filthiest, blackest heart and make it white as wool.

32:20.341 --> 32:20.421
Man.

32:20.441 --> 32:22.243
Isn't that a beautiful promise in a new year?

32:22.263 --> 32:23.766
I'm like, goodness.

32:25.027 --> 32:32.338
God says, if you'll just come to me, if we'll dial, if we just come and open your heart to me, let's settle this matter.

32:35.170 --> 32:35.991
Follow me.

32:36.472 --> 32:38.876
I will be your provider, your protector, your healer.

32:39.156 --> 32:43.222
All you have to do is admit you've lived by your own rules and it hasn't worked out so well.

32:44.925 --> 32:45.706
That's all you have to do.

32:46.026 --> 32:49.131
And now realize you need to and want to align with me.

32:49.171 --> 32:55.100
And when you live by your own rules, God says it's holding on to lead to heartache.

32:56.983 --> 32:57.784
But you come to Him.

32:58.986 --> 33:04.594
When you return to God, it leads to freedom, healing, joy, hope, rest, peace, all those things.

33:05.506 --> 33:06.187
We crave.

33:08.550 --> 33:16.522
In this new year, we all need a redeemer who can do what resolutions never can.

33:19.686 --> 33:24.814
In this new year, we long for a redeemer, not more resolutions.

33:27.398 --> 33:33.266
I invite Mark to come back up and help us with the end of this, just to give us some response time.

33:35.010 --> 33:38.755
God's message to us through Isaiah's clear friends.

33:40.858 --> 33:44.764
Rebellion from God brings heartache.

33:47.888 --> 33:51.493
That's just what happens.

33:53.776 --> 33:57.602
When we don't align our lives with God, it brings heartache.

34:01.848 --> 34:03.570
But when we align our lives,

34:04.930 --> 34:06.172
He promises to deliver.

34:06.212 --> 34:09.857
If we'll turn to Him, He promises to deliver.

34:09.877 --> 34:15.624
Have you turned to God in your life?

34:17.107 --> 34:17.787
Have you done that?

34:18.869 --> 34:29.944
If you've never turned to God and opened your heart to Him, boy, the New Year is a great time to do that.

34:29.964 --> 34:31.506
No one's sin is too big.

34:33.282 --> 34:35.404
No one's rebellion has gone on too long.

34:37.607 --> 34:39.950
No one's secret is too dark.

34:41.672 --> 34:43.033
It's just good news, friends.

34:43.914 --> 34:45.676
No one's shame is too mortifying.

34:47.318 --> 34:50.582
No one's wandered away and come back too many times.

34:51.263 --> 34:51.744
Done with you.

34:53.385 --> 34:54.206
It's not that way.

34:55.548 --> 34:56.329
It's not that way.

34:59.192 --> 35:00.754
God sees all of that.

35:01.442 --> 35:08.394
God sees all of it and he promises to forgive and to cleanse and to restore any and every heart who will come to him.

35:08.734 --> 35:09.796
Will you come to him today?

35:11.759 --> 35:23.819
Some of you, some of you in journeying with him for a long time and you're just filled with gratitude today for his faithfulness and you're experiencing that goodness and that blessing he promises.

35:24.160 --> 35:27.986
But there might be some of you in the room today who you realize this new year,

35:28.450 --> 35:33.697
In this new year, as you reflect on the last year, you realize there's areas of your life that aren't disrepair.

35:34.919 --> 35:39.405
There's areas of your connection with God that you've shelved.

35:40.727 --> 35:44.752
And so today is a perfect time for you to realign.

35:45.954 --> 35:48.137
God says, come, let's settle a matter.

35:49.879 --> 35:53.244
Get your heart right today, right?

35:55.006 --> 35:55.447
Let's pray.

35:57.450 --> 35:57.810
Lord,

35:58.754 --> 36:10.527
I know there are many in the room today who they hear your words through the prophet Isaiah and it's just affirming to them.

36:11.588 --> 36:14.672
They remember the dark days in their lives.

36:14.692 --> 36:22.600
They remember maybe days of rebellion and they remember what a radical change happened in their lives when they turned their hearts to you.

36:23.902 --> 36:25.003
And they're just saying thanks.

36:26.104 --> 36:27.826
They're just telling you how much they love you.

36:29.058 --> 36:30.120
and thankful for those.

36:31.562 --> 36:34.146
And also thankful for those in the room today who are here.

36:34.166 --> 36:41.918
And they've journeyed with you, but there's an area too out of their lives.

36:41.938 --> 36:51.272
In fact, they may have focused a resolution, their New Year's resolution on that area of their lives, that they want to bring back an alignment with you.

36:51.713 --> 36:52.915
God empower that in them.

36:53.255 --> 36:54.597
Fill them with your spirit.

36:57.141 --> 36:57.682
Don't let them

36:58.178 --> 37:03.063
Don't forget about that awareness of that spot that's out of alignment.

37:04.585 --> 37:07.108
Help them empower them to bring that back in alignment.

37:11.252 --> 37:14.816
And Lord, I pray for those in the room today who maybe for the first time are coming to you.

37:15.497 --> 37:19.301
They hear that call through the Prophet Isaiah, come let's settle this matter.

37:23.886 --> 37:27.570
No matter how rough it's been,

37:31.266 --> 37:33.093
You will bring renewal and restoration.

37:34.157 --> 37:35.683
You will bring forgiveness and healing.

37:40.100 --> 37:40.722
Thank you, Lord.

